#: data/royale/units.ruleset:188
#, fuzzy
msgid "?unitclass:Big Siege"
msgstr "지도자"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:516 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:508
msgid ""
"Settlers can also perform some of the same terrain alterations as Workers "
"(but cannot build airstrips, airbases, or buoys)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:557 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:549
msgid ""
"Migrants can be used to transfer population to other cities, but may not "
"found new cities. They can also perform some of the same terrain alterations "
"as Workers (but cannot build airstrips, airbases, or buoys)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:569
#, fuzzy
msgid "Immigrants"
msgstr "관개"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:601
msgid ""
"Immigrants can be used to transfer population to other cities, but may not "
"found new cities. They can also perform some of the same terrain alterations "
"as Workers."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:605
msgid ""
"TIP: Immigrants can be a good alternative to Workers in overpopulated "
"cities, as they benefit from free food upkeep."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:612
#, fuzzy
msgid "?unit:Tribal Workers"
msgstr "노동자"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:644
msgid ""
"The original workers are those you start the game with. You cannot build "
"original workers. While the original workers have less moves compared to the "
"workers the original workers have one major advantage. The enemy is not able "
"to capture the original workers. Only the workers you can build can be "
"captured. Workers have the ability to improve terrain tiles. See the help on "
"Terrain and Terrain Alterations for the effects of their actions."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:724
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If the player knows Invention, Engineers may also perform more radical "
"terrain transformations than Workers, Settlers, or Migrants, with the "
"\"transform\" order. Examples include conversion of Tundra into Plains, or "
"even Ocean into Swamp in some circumstances (when on board an ocean-going "
"vessel, on a tile surrounded by sufficient existing land). See the Terrain "
"Alterations section for more details."
msgstr ""
"기술자는 노동자와 비슷하지만, 그들은 두배나 빠르게 일하고, 이동합니다. 기술자"
"는 또한 노동자와 이주자의 능력으로 할 수 없는, 주요 지형 변화를 형성할 수 있"
"습니다. (예를 들어, 툰드라를 사막으로 변환합니다.); 지형 개조 구역의 도움말"
"에 더 상세하게 볼 수 있습니다.\n"
"\n"
"조언 1: 기술자가 평범한 노동자만큼 같은 자원을 요구하면, 가능할 때  노동자를 "
"기술자로 개선하십시오.\n"
"\n"
"조언 2: 만약 당신이 레오나르도의 작업장을 세워 관리한다면, 작업장이 더 이상 "
"쓸모가 없기 전에 폭약을 연구하십시오. 이 방법은, 당신의 노동자 부대가 공짜로 "
"개선 될 수 있습니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:830
msgid "Swordsmen"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:856
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Swordsmen are heavily armed and well disciplined infantry units with an "
"excellent offensive value."
msgstr ""
"보병은 중무장했고, 훌륭한 공격용의 가치와 함께, 잘 달련된 보병 부대입니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:965
msgid "Infantry"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:991
msgid ""
"Infantry are modern version of Riflemen, relatively good at defending your "
"cities.\n"
"\n"
"Why: This unit is the end of an upgrade path all the way from Warriors. It "
"is the best non-armored unit for defending your cities. This was added so "
"that the Riflemen could be upgraded into something else than Marines. "
"Upgading those and the previous units into Marines created issues to the "
"gameplay. The players were taking huge risks by building lots of cheap early "
"units. The plan was to uprade the early units at a later time for offensive "
"purposes. Upgrading the early units into Marines created situations where "
"the game ended (for some players) in a turn or two with no real warning. "
"With this one as the final upgrade the problem is no more because of this "
"upgrade path. The Infantry unit also allows an alternative research path "
"because of the reasonably good defense value."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1072
msgid ""
"Partisans are guerilla fighters who are experts at using the terrain to "
"their advantage. Partisans have no home city and units outside cities will "
"not be killed if the city building them is lost. Since partisans are "
"citizens trained to fight the oppressor they can once again become part of "
"the normal population when the war is over. The partisans are almost "
"invisible to the enemy but this comes with a cost. The partisans are not "
"that fast when moving to a new loaction."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1117
msgid ""
"Fundamentalist nations can maintain Fanatic units without having to pay any "
"upkeep nor causing military unhappiness. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1223 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1084
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Mechanized Infantry has the strongest inherent defensive strength of any "
"land unit, and is very fast on roads and easy terrain, but it is hindered "
"rather than helped by rough terrain (it cannot move into mountains, swamps, "
"or jungles), and it is only available near the end of the technology tree."
msgstr ""
"기계화 보병은 어느 지상 부대보다 가장 강한 방어력을 가졌지만, 기술 나무의 끝"
"의 근처에 도달해야만 유효합니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1291 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:1152
msgid ""
"Chariots are horse-pulled war wagons. They have a stronger attack than "
"Horsemen, but their speed comes at a cost: they are more expensive to build, "
"they cannot take advantage of terrain to defend themselves, they cannot move "
"in rough terrain (mountains, swamps, and jungles) without roads, and they "
"cannot be transported by sea using early ships (Triremes and Caravels)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1360
msgid ""
"Crusaders are highly disciplined mounted warriors driven by a higher cause. "
"Fundamentalist nations can maintain Crusader units without having to pay any "
"upkeep nor causing military unhappiness. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1523
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Catapults are large rock-throwing machines of war. They are very strong "
"attackers -- and even more powerful against cities -- but equally weak "
"defenders and will need an escort to be effective. Unescorted catapults may "
"be captured by the enemy."
msgstr ""
"투석기는 큰 돌을 던지는 전쟁 기계입니다. 그들은 매우 강한 공격자이지만, 마찬"
"가지로 방어자에게 약하고, 효과적이려면 호위가 필요할 수 있습니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1529
msgid ""
"While powerful, Catapults (and their successors) are bulky and awkward. They "
"require roads to move in rough terrain (mountains, swamps, and jungles), are "
"difficult to defend, and are too big for early ships (Triremes and "
"Caravels). Catapults and later siege units do not gain benefits from "
"Barracks. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1564
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Cannons are large firearms that can fire heavy projectiles over long "
"distances. As with the Catapults they replace, they are very strong "
"attackers -- and even more powerful against cities -- but equally weak "
"defenders and will need an escort to be effective, and have limited "
"mobility. Cannon and other siege units do not gain benefits from Barracks. "
"Unescorted cannons may be captured by the enemy. "
msgstr ""
"대포는 무거운 발사체를 긴 거리를 두고 발사할 수 있는, 큰 화기입니다. 그들은 "
"매우 강한 공격자이지만, 마찬가지로 방어자에게 약하고, 효과적이려면 호위가 필"
"요할 수 있습니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1600
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The artillery is an upgraded cannon. As with its predecessors, it is a very "
"strong attacker -- and even more powerful against cities -- but equally weak "
"defender and will need an escort to be effective, and has limited mobility. "
"Artillery and other siege units do not gain benefits from Barracks. "
"Unescorted artilleries may be captured by the enemy."
msgstr ""
"포는 대포에서 개선된 것입니다. 이것은 매우 강한 공격자이지만, 마찬가지로 방어"
"자에게 약하고, 효과적이려면 호위가 필요할 수 있습니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1635
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Howitzers are upgraded artillery with improved defensive as well as "
"offensive capabilities. However, they still have the limited mobility of "
"their predecessors. Like earlier siege units, Howitzers do not gain benefits "
"from Barracks."
msgstr ""
"곡사포는 공격 능력뿐만 아니라 방어의 향상과 함께, 포에서 개선된 것입니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1670
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fighters are your first airborne units. They can move anywhere and attack "
"any unit. The fighter will lose all moves when attacking another unit."
msgstr ""
"전투기는 당신의 최초의 공수 부대입니다. 그들은 어디든지 이동하고, 어느 부대"
"도 공격할 수 있습니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1673
msgid ""
"Fighters are very good for securing access from nations with no air units."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1708
msgid ""
"A Bomber's attack against units on land is a bombard attack; against units "
"on water it has a regular attack."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1711
msgid ""
"Bombers are very good for securing access from nations with no air units."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1859
msgid ""
"GUIDE: Since the Triremes are able to travel on rivers, the players are able "
"to use them for transporting military units for attacking riverside cities "
"deep inside homeland. The Trireme can only transport smaller units but the "
"Barge (obsoleting the Trireme) is able to move big siege units. Because of "
"the river travelling ability it is important to guard the coastal tiles with "
"rivers on them. The units loaded on triremes cannot attack (only Marines "
"can) from the ship if the ship is on an ocean tile, but if the ship moves on "
"a river tile the land units will be able to attack and also move without "
"losing all of the movepoints when unloading from the trireme. The same thing "
"applies to the Barge unit."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1874
msgid "Barge"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1901
msgid ""
"The Barge can travel on Ocean (but not Deep Ocean) and it can clean up "
"pollution. It is also able to move on rivers."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1909
msgid "Longboat"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1936
msgid ""
"The Longboat is your first deep ocean capable boat unit that only can carry "
"one Merchant or Small Land unit. It can act as a transport ship and has "
"rudimentary defensive and offensive capabilities. It is also unique and you "
"can only have one Longboat at a time. The Longboat is heavier than the  "
"Trireme and this allows it to travel on Deep Ocean but  not on rivers."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1945
msgid ""
"GUIDE: The longboat is very useful for exploring the oceans and since it is "
"able to carry Settlers, it can be used for establishing early colonies far "
"away from home. You can only have one Longboat at a time, but this is not as "
"limiting as you may think. The Longboat can take a Settler to a far away "
"land, unload the Settler, build a city with it and then you can disband the "
"Longboat in the new city. This way you can build a new Longboat at home and "
"will also get half of the shields back. Those can be used for building a "
"defensive unit or maybe a Workers for the new colony city."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1958
msgid "Square-Rigged Caravel"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1985
msgid ""
"A much larger version of the Caravel, it is most notorious because of heavy "
"offensive capabilities. Much of the focus on the design is on combat and "
"because of that it only has limited transport capacity even while it can "
"also carry those land units the regular Caravel cannot. In the early ages of "
"exploration it is great for keeping your coastals free of enemy ships."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:1992
msgid ""
"GUIDE: The Square-Rigged Caravel is able to carry only one unit but the unit "
"can be one of the heavy ones. This allows small and middle scale military "
"operations that may surprise your enemy. A fleet of these ships is expensive "
"to build, but the surprise attack may cripple an unprepared nation. This is "
"why a single ship loaded with a puny Warrior may devastate the enemy "
"economy. The enemy cannot see what is loaded on the ship and this is why "
"bluffing with this ship loaded with a weak unit may make your enemy afraid "
"and waste resources on building defenses."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2105
#, fuzzy
msgid "Flagship Frigate"
msgstr "프리깃함"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2131
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Frigate is a specialized ship with a strong offensive value, and can "
"attack units on land, but it cannot transport units. A Flagship Frigate is "
"more powerful, slightly faster and more expensive. You can have only one "
"unit of this type at a time and it cannot be bribed."
msgstr "순양함은 강하고 공격적인 배 부대입니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2272
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The AEGIS Cruiser is equipped with an advanced defensive missile system.  "
"Airborne units are at a disadvantage against AEGIS Cruisers."
msgstr "이지스 순양함은 진보된 미사일 방어 체계를 장비합니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2348
#, fuzzy
msgid "Nuclear Submarine"
msgstr "핵겨울"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2376
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Traveling under the surface of the ocean, Submarines have a very high "
"strategic value, but a weak defense if caught off guard. The Nuclear "
"Submarine is also able to carry <issiles."
msgstr ""
"잠수함은 바다의 표면 아래로 여행하므로, 아주 높은 전략적인 가치를 가집니디"
"만, 만약 발각된다면 방어에 약합니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2380
msgid ""
"GUIDE: The Nuclear Submarine is able to carry Missile units. A chain of "
"several Nuclear Submarines can be used to transport Nuclear Missiles almost "
"anywhere really fast. This makes them extremely dangerous. Like the Non-"
"nuclear Submarines these units use fuel and need refueling. This is why you "
"may need allies for refueling the submarines if they are far from home. "
"Another option is to get remote colony cities you can use as Submarine "
"bases. Since the Nuclear Submarines have no home city they can retaliate "
"even if you lose all your coastal cities supporting your other naval units."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2422 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2060
msgid ""
"It can transport aircraft and military land units (not wheeled), although "
"land units cannot always be transferred to and from Helicopters while "
"onboard (see Helicopter help)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2459
msgid "elite 3 (350%)"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2468 data/sandbox/units.ruleset:2107
msgid ""
"Transports can also clean pollution and fallout on water tiles, and with "
"knowledge of Miniaturization, may build oil platforms on deep ocean tiles "
"(for use by Offshore Platforms)."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2503
msgid "The Missile is a missile unit able to shoot down enemy air units."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2505
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"TIP: A handful of these may successfully keep the air around your treasured "
"homeland free of enemy air units."
msgstr ""
"순항 미사일은 적 영토 안으로 깊숙하게 충돌하는 장-거리 미사일입니다.\n"
"\n"
"조언: 소수의 이들은 적 함선들로부터 당신의 소중한 조국 주위의 영해를 성공적으"
"로 지킬 수 있습니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2508
msgid ""
"GUIDE: The Missile units have poor vision so you may want to use Fighters or "
"other air units for scouting the area before attacking. Few Missile units "
"can be used as the backbone of your air defense strategy before you get "
"better Fighters. The enemy Fighters and Bombers will lose all moves when "
"attacking so they will remain at the same place until the next turn. This is "
"when you can use the Missile for shooting down the airplanes attacking you. "
"The Nuclear Submarines and Carriers can also move the Missile units. Use "
"this to your advantage and you may need less Missiles to cover your air "
"defense needs with the short range missile units."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2560
#, fuzzy
msgid "Intercontinental Missile"
msgstr "순항 미사일"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2587
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Intercontinental Missile is an ultra long-distance missile that can "
"strike extremely deep into enemy territory."
msgstr ""
"기수는 말을 탄 전사이고, 적 영토에 깊게 침투하는 초기의 기습 부대입니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2590
msgid ""
"TIP: These extremely powerful missiles can reach almost any place on the map."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2593
msgid ""
"GUIDE: The missile units have poor vision so you may want to use Fighters or "
"other air units for scouting the area before attacking. The Intercontinental "
"Missiles can remain in air for several turns. Together with AWACS planes or "
"maybe hidden Submarines (for vision) on the enemy coastal areas it is "
"possible to launch a devastating attack virtually anywhere on the map. Since "
"the Intercontinental Missile can be killed by a missile unit, you may want "
"to launch several of them at once so that the enemy is not able to kill them "
"all if the attack is noticed. This late game unit is also very good at "
"sinking the enemy ships. This is why extra caution is needed if your enemy "
"is able to build these beasts."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2607
#, fuzzy
msgid "Nuclear Bomb"
msgstr "핵병기"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2639
msgid ""
"You can build the Nuclear Bomb unit when you have the required advance, and "
"the Manhattan Project wonder has been built by any player. However, without "
"further technology the nuclear units cannot move on their own.  The Nuclear "
"Bomb is unique and each nation can have only one at a time."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2648
#, c-format
msgid ""
"On impact, the blast will destroy any unit in an area 3 tiles wide (3x3 "
"squares for rectangular grids), including friendly units. Any city within "
"the blast area loses 30% of its population, and land tiles within the blast "
"area are subject to nuclear fallout. The tiles have 20% chance of losing "
"infrastructure and has a 20% chance of destroying city improvements. "
"(Improvements which have less than 100% sabotage chance are not destroyed)"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2659 data/royale/units.ruleset:2723
msgid ""
"TIP: You may be involved in a situation where you have invaded an enemy "
"country en masse, but the enemy cities are too strong. Before using a "
"Nuclear unit, assemble a gang of cleanup units next to the city and have "
"them ready to fix the fallout on the same turn it occurs! This minimizes the "
"chance of nuclear winter."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2705
msgid ""
"With Advanced Flight, all Nuclear units (including those already built) gain "
"a range of 9 movement points, and Rocketry increases this to 18."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2709
#, c-format
msgid ""
"On impact, the blast will destroy any unit in an area 3 tiles wide (3x3 "
"squares for rectangular grids), including friendly units. Any city within "
"the blast area loses 30% of its population, and land tiles within the blast "
"area are subject to nuclear fallout. The tiles have 20% chance of losing "
"infrastructure and  has a 20% chance of destroying city improvements. "
"(Improvements which have less than 100% sabotage chance are not destroyed)"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2717
msgid ""
"Similar to pollution and global warming, the risk of global nuclear winter "
"increases with fallout. If nuclear winter occurs, terrain across the globe "
"changes into desert, tundra, and ice. Settlers, Migrants, Workers, and "
"Engineers and (for fallout on water) Transports can clean up nuclear fallout."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2879
msgid ""
"She can perform all the functions of the Diplomat. Refer to the Diplomat "
"entry for more details. Unlike a Diplomat, a Spy may also survive an "
"operation in a foreign city and become more experienced as a result. Spies "
"are also more effective than Diplomats at defending cities against foreign "
"Diplomats and Spies. "
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2885
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A Spy can also be used to:\n"
"\n"
" - sabotage an enemy unit (reducing its hit points to half), if it is alone "
"on a tile and the players are at war;\n"
" - poison the water supply of an enemy city (reducing the population by one "
"and emptying the granary);\n"
" - sabotage predetermined city targets (with a reduced chance of success)."
msgstr ""
"간첩은 간첩 행위의 기술을 그녀의 이전의 외교관보다 더 많이 배웠습니다.\n"
"\n"
"그녀는 외교관의 모든 기능들을 수행할 수 있습니다; 외교관의 자리를 더 많은 세"
"부 사항들로 나타냅니다. 외교관과 다르게, 간첩은 외국 도시안의 작전에서 살아남"
"고 결과적으로 경험이 더 쌓입니다. 또한 간첩들은 외교관들보다 외국 외교관들과 "
"간첩들에 대항할 때 더 효과적입니다.\n"
"\n"
"간첩은 사용될 수도 있습니다:\n"
" - 적 부대를 사보타주하기 (이것의 타격 점수를 반으로 줄입니다), 부대가 타일 "
"위에 혼자있고 플레이어들이 전쟁중이어야 합니다;\n"
" - 적 도시의 물 공급에 독을 넣기 (인구를 1 단위 줄이고 곡창을 비웁니다);\n"
" - 특정한 기술 훔치기 (성공의 기회가 줄어듭니다);\n"
" - 더 나아간 기술들을 이미 도난당한 도시로 부터 훔치기 (도시들은 그들이 도난"
"당한 때 부터 매 차례 더 잘 견디더라도 입니다);\n"
" - 예정된 도시 대상들을 사보타주하기 (성공의 기회가 줄어듭니다).\n"
"\n"
"더 공격적인 행동들(사보타주, 절도, 봉기 선동, 그리고 독을 넣기)로 살아남는 간"
"첩은 가장 가까운 친근한 도시의 안전한 곳으로 탈출합니다."

