#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2967
msgid ""
"An Operative that survives the more aggressive actions (sabotage, theft, "
"inciting rebellion, and poisoning) escapes to the safety of the nearest "
"friendly city."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2971
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Operatives built under Communist or Federation governments will start at the "
"first veteran level (handler)."
msgstr "게임 차례당 하나의 구식인 부대를 개선시킵니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:2980
msgid "Scribe"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3012
msgid ""
"The Scribe wanders foreign lands seeking new knowledge to share in his "
"native country."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3014
msgid "The actions available to Scribes in a foreign city are:"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3016
msgid ""
"  - \"Steal Technology\" / \"Industrial Espionage\": Your unit attempts to "
"learn the secrets of a random or chosen technology known to the city's owner "
"but not to you. Trying to steal a  particular technology is much less likely "
"to succeed than trying to steal a random  technology (\"At Scribe's "
"discretion\"). Also, every time technology is stolen from a city, the "
"chances of further espionage attempts succeeding at that particular city go "
"down. This action may be attempted even when not at war, but will cause a "
"diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3024
msgid ""
"Like Spies, Scribes have small chance of returning after a successful "
"mission, but are often lost after a mission. Foreign Diplomats and Spies "
"will defend against the Scribe as against other Spy actions."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3028
msgid ""
"GUIDE: With no traditional tech trading the only way to get techs from other "
"players is using the Scribe unit. Instead trading through diplomacy the "
"players can trade or steal techs by using the Scribe unit. Diplomats, Spies, "
"and Operatives cannot steal techs, but they can defend the cities against "
"Scribes trying to steal techs. This is why it is best to use those units for "
"investigating the city and also for killing the defending Diplomats, Spies, "
"and Operatives. Only the Scribe and other units like it are able to steal "
"techs."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3041
msgid "Scholar"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3073
msgid ""
"The Scholar wanders foreign lands seeking new knowledge to share in his "
"native country."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3075
msgid "The actions available to Scholar in a foreign city are:"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3077
msgid ""
"  - \"Steal Technology\" / \"Industrial Espionage\": Your unit attempts to "
"learn the secrets of a random or chosen technology known to the city's owner "
"but not to you. Trying to steal a particular technology is much less likely "
"to succeed than trying to steal a random technology (\"At Scholar's "
"discretion\"). Also, every time technology is stolen from a city, the "
"chances of further espionage attempts succeeding at that particular city go "
"down. This action may be attempted even when not at war, but will cause a "
"diplomatic incident."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3085
msgid ""
"Like Spies, Scholars have small chance of returning after a successful "
"mission, but are often lost after a mission. Foreign Diplomats and Spies "
"will defend against the Scholar as against other Spy actions."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3088
msgid ""
"GUIDE: With no traditional tech trading the only way to get techs from other "
"players is using the Scholar or other tech trading unit. Instead trading "
"through diplomacy the players can trade or steal techs by using the Scholar "
"unit. Diplomats, Spies, and Operatives cannot steal techs, but they can "
"defend the cities against Scholars trying to steal techs. This is why it is "
"best to use those units for investigating the city and also for killing the "
"defending Diplomats, Spies, and Operatives. Only the Scholar and other units "
"like it are able to steal techs."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3133
#, fuzzy
msgid "Establishing trade routes is not enabled in this ruleset."
msgstr ""
"미안한, 당신의 %s (은)는 이것이 고향이 없기 때문에 하나의 무역 경로를 설립하"
"지 못합니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3207
msgid ""
"Explorers can also perform some actions in another player's city, although "
"the unit disappears after the action is complete. This text is left here  as "
"a reminder that they could do this if the ruleset would allow it."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3211
msgid " - \"Establish Embassy\": This action is not enabled in this game."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3213
msgid " - \"Investigate City\": This action is not enabled in this game."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3215
msgid ""
"GUIDE: The Explorer can be used to break the Zones of Control (ZoC) if an "
"enemy unit is blocking you. This can be very useful in situations where the "
"enemy is trying to limit your options by placing fortified units in "
"strategic locations next to rivers or roads. Simply move the Explorer to a "
"tile you want to go to and you can move unit(s) to a tile already occupied "
"by your own unit. The Explorer is also very good for checking who is next to "
"you and how far your enemies have already expanded. Many players consider "
"killing an Explorer as an act of war. This is why it sometimes makes sense "
"to warn before killing the explorer."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3347
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fusion Fighter"
msgstr "핵융합"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3375
#, fuzzy
msgid "An improved Stealth Fighter, with a higher movement radius."
msgstr "향상된 공격력과 높은 이동 반경을 가진, 향상된 전투기입니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3383
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fusion Bomber"
msgstr "핵융합"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3410
#, fuzzy
msgid "An improved Stealth Bomber, with a higher movement radius."
msgstr "향상된 공격력과 높은 이동 반경을 가진, 향상된 폭격기입니다."

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3419
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fusion Battleship"
msgstr "전함"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3445
msgid ""
"A battleship powered by fusion power that attacks with triple firepower."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3453
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fusion Armor"
msgstr "핵융합"

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3479
msgid "A fusion powered Armor attacking with double firepower."
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3487
msgid "Cargo Aircraft"
msgstr ""

#: data/royale/units.ruleset:3514
msgid ""
"The Cargo Aircraft is an airplane with an exceptionally high range while "
"carrying a heavy cargo. It is able to transport a wide range of units able "
"to surprise your enemy. This exceptionally heavy airplane has no offecive "
"capabilities but is able to defend."
msgstr ""

#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:86
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A city with an Airport can airlift an extra unit per turn. Airlifting "
"instantly transports the unit from one city to another and will use  all of "
"the unit's movement points. A unit must have some movement  points left to "
"be airlifted, and cannot carry cargo."
msgstr ""
"도시의 숙련자인 공중 부대의 생산을 허용합니다.(헬리콥터를 포함해서 입니다.) "
"또한, 손상받은 공중 부대가 도시 안에서 한 차례 움직임 없이 머무르면 완전히 회"
"복됩니다. (다시 말해서, 헬리콥터를 포함해서 입니다.)\n"
"\n"
"2개의 도시와 함께 있는 공항은, 매 차례당 하나의 부대가 공수 할 수 있습니다. "
"공수는 즉시 한 부대를 다른 도시로 모든 부대의 움직임에 설정 할 수 있습니다. "
"한 부대가 공수되기 위해서 반드시 몇몇의 이동점이 필요합니다."

#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:91
msgid ""
"Two cities with Airports can airlift medium and heavy weight units once "
"Advanced Flight and Fusion Power are discovered."
msgstr ""

#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:213
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Increases the luxury good and tax output in a city by an additional 50%. "
"With both a Bank and a Marketplace in a city, the total bonus is 100%."
msgstr "도시 안의 복지와 세금의 생산량을 50% 로 증가시킵니다."

#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:474
msgid ""
"When any small city grows or shrinks, 10 food points are saved. This helps "
"cities to grow faster and more easily withstand famine. With a Granary this "
"is extended to cities of size 4 and above. (10 food points is half what a "
"small city needs to grow, but more points are needed for later growth steps.)"
msgstr ""

#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:532 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:672
#: data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:863 data/sandbox/buildings.ruleset:1018
#, fuzzy, c-format
msgid ""
"Any kind of electrical plant increases the shield production effects of a "
"Factory or Mfg. Plant in its city by 25% each. Thus, an electrical plant in "
"combination with either a Factory or Mfg. Plant gives a 50% production bonus "
"over the level without any of these improvements. An electrical plant, "
"Factory, and Mfg. Plant together give a 100% production bonus. The extra "
"production may lead to the city generating more pollution."
msgstr ""
"공장과 제조공장의 효과를 증가시킵니다. 도시의 보호 생산에 지어집니다. 발전소"
"는 공장이나 제조공장과 결합됩니다.  발전소는 이 결합(발전소, 공장, 그리고 제"
"조공장)없이는 75% 의 생산 보너스를 줍니다. 발전소가 위의 결합과 함께라면 "
"150% 의 생산 보너스를 줍니다. 추가적인 생산은 도시에 공해를, 더 발생하도록 이"
